<Content>Good value in the university area The apartments are useful for a stay of several days, as you get a living area and kitchenette and balcony, but it lacks double glazing and can be somewhat noisy... the tile floors give them a cold look, though fine in summer. Shower heads were very poor. Breakfast was nice, as were the staff. A colleague was staying on the top floor and got a room, or what seemed like a suite, with a fantastic bathroom and lovely bed. I would recommend to take this if possible! 10 minute walk from the metro. 
