<Author>daniellugsden
<Content>good quality We stayed three nights at the victoria suites which is located on avra pedrables very near in the Nou Camp in Barcelona. The hotel has a four star standard and i think that was fair. Staff are very helpful, rooms are large, modern and have self catering facilites as well as large bathroom and living area. The hotel is located around a ten minutes walk from the football stadium and around 8 euros in a taxi from la rambla (centre of barcelona)Maria christina is the nearest metro stop which is a 5 minute walk down the diagonal (main street from hotel). A ticket for ten journeys is 6 euros which is well worth it. The best stop to get off for la rambla is Catalunya which is just at the top of this street and opposite the hard rock cafe. They ae so many good restaurant and bars and we tended to go around the plaza real which is (when walking down la rambla) on the rights by macdonaldsOverall the hotel was great and a good time was had by all 
