<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Not what I expected from a 4* We've just returned from a weeks holiday in Barcelona. Myself, hubby and 2 kids. Hotel looked very nice from the outside. Reception area nice and clean, nothing special though. The room was quite big - a living area, 2 bedrooms and bathroom. Quite spacious but also very basic the rooms were clean. Swimmng pool was closed whilst we stayed there which was quite annoying although access to the pool was next to the main hotel entrance. Had breakfast only on the first day - quite disappointed with the choice and quality of food on offer, 10 euros per person too expensive !!!. The most annoying thing we found was the noise - we could hear people walking in the room above us; cars/lorries outside especially at around 11pm when the dustbin men come to empty the recycle bottle bins every night.. Would not rate this hotel as a 4 star - definitely 3 star. Would not go back although barcelona has limited family or hotels with adjoining rooms.Location was just outside the main city area very quiet and safe walked around at midnight no problems people and restaurants in area very nice. 10 mins from NU Camp and 5 min from tube station and bus stops including main tourist red route. Childrens small play area just outside hotel which the kids enjoyed. overall a okay hotel just spoilt by the breakfast, noise and lack of atmosphere. 
